      "author": "eharris128",
      "description": "## What's new\n\n### ✨ LinkedIn ribbon icon\nThe ribbon icon is now the recognizable LinkedIn \"in\" bug instead of the generic send glyph, so Content OS is easy to tell apart from other plugins' ribbon icons (such as Obsidian Publish). The icon follows your active theme color. (#3)\n\n### 🔧 Maintenance\n- Updated all dependencies to their latest versions. (#4)\n- Added a `SECURITY.md` security policy.\n\n## Install / update\nThis release ships the built `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css`. Update via the Obsidian Community Plugins browser, or download the attached assets into your `.obsidian/plugins/content-os/` folder.\n\n**Full changelog:** https://github.com/eharris128/obsidian-content-os/compare/1.0.3...1.0.4\n",
